Others: The Milwaukee Bucks lost to the Portland Trail Blazers with a score of 105-102.
The loss put the Bucks in a tie with the Heat for fifth in the East.
Giannis Antetokounmpo offered a strange analogy about his play following the loss, comparing it to a savings account in the minus.
Antetokounmpo thinks he needs to get back to being a stronger player and playing with more aggressiveness.
The Bucks can't afford too many more losses like this against bad teams as they are just one game ahead of the ninth spot in the East.
